The National Assembly elections held alongside the Presidential election last week Saturday and we have compiled the list of those elected into the House of Representatives from Borno State. Lawmakers-elect from Borno State are: 1. Hon. Ibrahim Abunna Lawan, Mafa, Konduga and Dikwa. (APC) 2. Dr. Zainab Gimba Bama, Ngala and Kala-Balge.(APC) 3. Engr. Satomi Ahmed Jere. (APC) 4. Hon. Aliyu Betera Biu, Bayo, Kwaya-Kuzar and Shani. (APC) 5. Dr. Haurna Mshelia Hawul and Askira/Uba.(APC) 6. Hon. Ahmadu Usman Jaha Chibok, Damboa and Gwoza. (APC) 7. Hon. Usman Zanna Kaga, Magumeri and Gubio. (APC) 8. Bar. Mohammed T. Monguno Marte, Kukawa and Monguno. (APC) 9. Hon Abdulkadir Rahis Maiduguri Metroplis Council. (APC)  10. Hon. Bukar Gana Kareto Mobar, Guzamala, and Abadam.(APC) 5 ex-aides of Borno governor win Reps' seats Shettima’s 5 ex-aides head to NASS Borno APC adopts indirect primaries